igaContent.name: IA-ROBOT-TESTING
igaContent.pSIDescription:
Price Sensitive Information (PSI) is information: 
 of a precise nature 
 which has not been made public 
 relating directly or indirectly to one or more issuers or to one or more financial instruments 
 which, if it were made public, would be likely to have a significant effect on the prices of those financial instruments or on the price of related derivative financial instruments. 
 Kindly attend the Mandatory PSI training CRegO Academy - Price Sensitive Information on Connect2Learn, before making a selection. 
 For more information, please refer to the Information Barrier Policy.
